verbose_text: (p < 0.001) The higher values of plasma homocysteine levels in Buerger 's disease patients and simultaneously the higher prevalence of tobacco usage in this group (90.9% of cases) and also higher plasma levels of homocysteine in smoker cases of 3 groups was compared to the initial measurement in all patients, suggests that tobacco could be the principle cause of hyperhomocysteinemia in such patients, which also has been revealed in other studies.
